        "title": "feat(control-plane): add tranche A/B registry and CI gate",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Add control-plane Tranche A+B scaffolding for contracts, schemas, registries, queues, reports, artifacts, dashboards, and ledgers.\n- Add Tranche B registries: `registries/schemas.registry.json`, `registries/validators.registry.json`, and `registries/policies.registry.json`.\n- Add a read-only CI gate at `.github/workflows/control-plane-validate.yml` that runs only `node scripts/validate_openclaw_control_plane.cjs` on `pull_request` and pushes to `main`.\n- Extend `scripts/validate_openclaw_control_plane.cjs` to enforce registry existence, path resolution, policy required fields (`id/version/status/decision/applies_to/reason`), allowed status values (`active|deprecated|experimental|blocked`), workflow contract/validator registration checks, secret-like config checks, and PHI marker checks for artifacts.\n\n## Verification\n- `node scripts/validate_openclaw_control_plane.cjs`\n  - Result: `PASS` (`findings: []`)\n- `pnpm lint:scripts`\n  - Result: `Found 0 warnings and 0 errors.`\n\n## Real behavior proof\nBehavior addressed: Control-plane Tranche A+B registry + policy + CI gate enforcement, including doctor-lane wrapper execution and machine-checkable validator policy.\nReal environment tested: Real local OpenClaw setup (non-mock), using the doctor wrapper lane added in this tranche.\nExact steps or command run after this patch: `bash scripts/openclaw-doctor-lint.sh`; `node scripts/validate_openclaw_control_plane.cjs`; `pnpm lint:scripts`.\nEvidence after fix: Running `bash scripts/openclaw-doctor-lint.sh` produced runtime outputs and wrote `reports/openclaw-doctor/doctor-lint-20260603-210912.json` plus a ledger event in `ledgers/operational_ledger.ndjson` (`event: openclaw_doctor_lint`, `artifact: reports/openclaw-doctor/doctor-lint-20260603-210912.json`).\nObserved result after fix: The control-plane wrapper executed end-to-end on a real OpenClaw setup and emitted governed artifacts/ledger entries; validator remains PASS and script lint passes after fixing the two lint violations.\nWhat was not tested: Tranche C surfaces (dashboard UI, queue processors, cost monitors, observability persistence, review workbench, promotion UI) were intentionally out of scope.\n\n## References\n- Conversation: https://app.warp.dev/conversation/ac14c3af-59df-48d6-961b-57f906c660ab\n\nCo-Authored-By: Oz <oz-agent@warp.dev>\n\n",
